import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def process_image(image_path):
    img = cv.imread(image_path)
    height, width, channels = img.shape
    file_size = np.prod(img.shape)
    
    print(f'Image Analysis: {width}x{height} pixels, {channels} channels')
    print(f'File Size on Disk: {file_size} bytes')
    
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Image')
    plt.show()

new_image_path = 'img/1.jpg'

process_image(new_image_path)

Image Analysis: 1920x1080 pixels, 3 channels
File Size on Disk: 6220800 bytes

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def process_grayscale_image(image_path):
    img = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
    height, width = img.shape
    image_size_bytes = img.nbytes
    
    print(f'Image Size in Pixels: {width}x{height}')
    print(f'Memory Footprint on Disk: {image_size_bytes} bytes')
    
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title('Grayscale Image')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

image_path = 'img/1.jpg'

process_grayscale_image(image_path)

Image Size in Pixels: 1920x1080
Memory Footprint on Disk: 2073600 bytes

import cv2
import math
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os

def resize_and_show_image(input_path, output_path):
    img = cv2.imread(input_path)
    
    print(f'Original Image Size: {img.shape[1]}x{img.shape[0]} ')
    print(f'Memory Footprint on Disk: {img.size} bytes')

    rows, cols = img.shape[:2]
    new_rows = math.floor(rows / 2)
    new_cols = math.floor(cols / 2)

    resized_img = cv2.resize(img, (new_cols, new_rows), interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(resized_img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title('Resized Image')
    plt.show()

    cv2.imwrite(output_path, resized_img)
    print(f'Resized Image Size: {new_cols}x{new_rows} pixels')

    file_size = os.path.getsize(output_path)
    print(f'File Size on Disk for Resized Image: {file_size} bytes')

input_img_path = 'img/1.jpg'
output_img_path = 'img/2.jpg'

resize_and_show_image(input_img_path, output_img_path)

Original Image Size: 1920x1080 
Memory Footprint on Disk: 6220800 bytes

Resized Image Size: 960x540 pixels
File Size on Disk for Resized Image: 190276 bytes

import cv2
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os

def resize_and_display_image(input_path, output_path, target_width):
    image = cv2.imread(input_path)
    
    height, width, channels = image.shape
    new_height = int(height * (target_width / width))

    resized_image = cv2.resize(image, (target_width, new_height), interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)

    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(resized_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(' ')
    plt.show()

    cv2.imwrite(output_path, resized_image)
    print(f"  : {target_width}x{new_height} ")

    file_size = os.path.getsize(output_path)
    print(f"     : {file_size} ")

input_image_path = 'img/1.jpg'
output_image_path = 'img/1.5.jpg'
target_width = 300

resize_and_display_image(input_image_path, output_image_path, target_width)

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def apply_affine_transform(input_path, output_path, input_points, output_width, output_height):
    img = cv.imread(input_path)

    if img is None:
        print("Error: Unable to load the image.")
    else:
        output_points = np.float32(
            [
                [0, 0],                  
                [output_width, 0],       
                [0, output_height]       
            ]
        )

        affine_transform_matrix = cv.getAffineTransform(input_points, output_points)
        img_affine_transformed = cv.warpAffine(img, affine_transform_matrix, (output_width, output_height))

        img_rgb = cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        plt.subplot(121)
        plt.imshow(img_rgb)
        plt.title('Input') 

        img_affine_transformed_rgb = cv.cvtColor(img_affine_transformed, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        plt.subplot(122)
        plt.imshow(img_affine_transformed_rgb)
        plt.title('Affine Transformation')

        cv.imwrite(output_path, img_affine_transformed)
        plt.show()

input_points = np.float32(
    [
        [60, 150],       
        [940, 150],   
        [60, 810]    
    ]
)
output_width = 800
output_height = 600

output_path = 'img/output_photo.jpg'

apply_affine_transform('img/photo.jpg', output_path, input_points, output_width, output_height)

import cv2 as cv

    if img is None:
        print("Error: Unable to load the image.")
    else:

            [

            ]
        )

        affine_transform_matrix = cv.getAffineTransform(input_points, output_points)
        img_affine_transformed = cv.warpAffine(img, affine_transform_matrix, (output_width, output_height))

        img_rgb = cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        plt.subplot(121)
        plt.imshow(img_rgb)
        plt.title('Input')

    [
